# TASK: Convert the provided lecture scribe into a properly formatted LaTeX document\
\
I have a lecture scribe (plain text) that was generated in a previous step. I need you to convert it into a **complete, compilable LaTeX document** while preserving the content **exactly** as given \'96 no additions, deletions, or edits of any kind.\
\
## Input\
I will paste the lecture scribe text below this prompt. It contains definitions, theorems, proofs, examples, and mathematical notation.\
\
## Output Requirements\
- Produce a **single LaTeX code block** containing a complete document with a proper preamble.\
- The LaTeX document must be compilable (e.g., with `pdflatex`) without errors.\
- Use appropriate LaTeX environments for structured content:\
  - `\\begin\{definition\}...\\end\{definition\}` for definitions\
  - `\\begin\{theorem\}...\\end\{theorem\}` for theorems\
  - `\\begin\{proof\}...\\end\{proof\}` for proofs\
  - `\\begin\{example\}...\\end\{example\}` for examples\
  - `\\begin\{align*\}...\\end\{align*\}` or similar for equations\
- Include necessary packages: `amsmath`, `amssymb`, `amsthm`, `geometry` for margins, and `graphicx` if needed (though no images are expected).\
- Use `\\section\{\}`, `\\subsection\{\}` etc. to match the scribe's structure.\
- Format all mathematical expressions correctly (e.g., `$P(A|B) = \\frac\{P(A \\cap B)\}\{P(B)\}$`).\
- Preserve the exact wording, ordering, and all content from the input. Do **not** rephrase, summarize, or add any new text.\
- If the scribe contains plain-text representations of math (like `P(A|B) = P(A\uc0\u8745 B)/P(B)`), convert them to proper LaTeX math.\
- The final LaTeX should have a title, author (set as "Scribe Notes" or similar), and date.\
\
## Important Constraints\
- **Do not alter the content** \'96 only change the formatting to LaTeX.\
- **Do not add any commentary** outside the LaTeX code block.\
- The output must be ready for me to copy into a `.tex` file and compile.\
\
